Thank you for the patch [~haibochen].
{code}
271	  public static final boolean DEFAULT_RM_SCHEDULER_OVERSUBSCRIPTION_ENABLED
272	      = true;
{code}
I think the default should be false.
{code}
385	      If set to true, the scheduler will try to over-allocate resources on
386	      the nodes that allow overallocation.
{code}
Could you be more specific here? It is unclear to me based on this description, how a node allows overallocation.
